#)what is elasticSearch?
Elasticsearch in Liferay is the default search engine used to index and search all portal content.

#)How can you apply Elasticsearch in a custom entity?
1)Create a custom entity using Service Builder and define all required fields inside service.xml.
2)Create an Indexer class for the custom entity that extends BaseIndexer<YourEntity>.
3)Implement the constructor DealIndexer() and inside it:
 -)Set default selected fields for indexing.
 -)Enable permission-aware search with setPermissionAware(true).
 -)Enable filter support with setFilterSearch(true).
4)Override the hasPermission method to ensure users can only see records they are allowed to access.
5)Override important Indexer methods:
-)doGetDocument() → add entity fields to the Elasticsearch index.
-)doGetSummary() → define how results appear in search summaries.
-)doReindex() → support reindexing of records.
-)doDelete() → remove documents from the index when a record is deleted.
After deploying the module, Liferay automatically indexes the entity in Elasticsearch whenever a record is added, updated, or deleted.
